    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span id=\"page195R_mcid11\" class=\"markedContent\"><span dir=\"ltr\">Keycards are small</span> <span dir=\"ltr\">plastic</span> <span dir=\"ltr\">cards about the size of playing </span><span dir=\"ltr\">cards, that contain coded information about their </span><span dir=\"ltr\">bearers and grant them access to secure areas.</span> <br /><span dir=\"ltr\">All </span><span dir=\"ltr\">keycards are assigned to a certain Data Server, which </span><span dir=\"ltr\">holds all records and access levels of a certain Keycard.</span><br /><span dir=\"ltr\">Most new era businesses, buildings or technologies </span><span dir=\"ltr\">require Keycard access instead of Lock and Key access. <br />A </span><span dir=\"ltr\">Shinobi with a Blank keycard an</span><span dir=\"ltr\">d a Hackers Kit could </span><span dir=\"ltr\">potentially fake (or spoof) the correct access credentials </span><span dir=\"ltr\">to access a previously inaccessible area.</span></span></p>",
